<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-export SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/evernote-export4.dtd">
<en-export export-date="20260611T073929Z" application="Evernote" version="11.9.1">
  <note>
    <title>Acute and chronic cholecystitis, ruptured.</title>
    <created>20191114T074133Z</created>
    <updated>20230606T081340Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Acute and chronic cholecystitis, ruptured.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections reveal partial mucosal destruction and inflamed</div><div>wall that is infiltrated by numerous polymorphonuclear as</div><div>well as mononuclear cells in its lamina propia as well as</div><div>the underlying muscular coat. The wall shows edema,</div><div>hyperemia and extravasation of RBCs. Focal transmural</div><div>necrosis is seen consistent with rupture.</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Acute hepatitis;</title>
    <created>20170804T005324Z</created>
    <updated>20231108T073047Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show liver tissue strips with lobular hepatocellular injury, featuring</div><div>lobular inflammation of neutrophils and lymphocytes accompanied by hepatocellular</div><div>swelling with presence of acidophilic bodies. Mild portal inflammation is noted.</div><div>Masson trichrome stain shows pericellular fibrosis as well as fibrous expansion of</div><div>some portal areas.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunostainings for CD3 and CD20 show no evidence of malignant lymphoma. The overall</div><div>features are consistent with acute hepatitis. Further serology test for viral loads is</div><div>suggested.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Adenocarcinoma</title>
    <created>20180313T011552Z</created>
    <updated>20231117T082809Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Liver, echo-guide biopsy --- Adenocarcinoma, moderately </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">to pooly differentiated. See Comment.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Comment:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Combined with the clinical history, image, tumor </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">histopathological feature and IHC stain profile, the</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">possible tumor origin of pancreatobiliary system and upper </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">gastrointestinal tract should be firstly consisdered.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Metastatic pancreatic adenocarcinoma can be compatible. </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Further clinicopathological correlation and study are</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">suggested.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181109T101147Z</created>
    <updated>20231117T082813Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>adenocarcinoma (please see description).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows hepatic tissue infiltrated by tumor cells with hyperchromatic nuclei arranged as irregular glandular structures in a desmoplastic stroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for CK7 and CK19, but not CK20 or arginase-1. CDX2 is positive in scattered, individual tumor cells.</div><div><br/></div><div>Taken together, this is an adenocarcinoma, of either primary or metastatic. It can be consistent with cholangiocarcinoma if the possibility of pancreatobiliary or gastrointestinal tract origin is excluded. Clinico-radiological correlation isrecommended.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170622T092336Z</created>
    <updated>20231117T082809Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Adenocarcinoma, primary or metastatic</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>It shows infiltrative tumor cells with hyperchromatic nuclei arranged as irregular</div><div>glandular structures with presence of tumor necrosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for CK19, but negative for</div><div>arginase-1. Taken together, this is an adenocarcinoma, either primary or metastatic.</div><div>Detailed systemic surveys are highly recommended.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Adenoma</title>
    <created>20170227T030151Z</created>
    <updated>20170227T030227Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>An adenoma with papillary / tubular pattern, lined by intestinal/ biliary / pyloric -type epithelium with low-grade dysplasia is seen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Autolysis (gallbladder)</title>
