      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The gallbladder shows mucosal autolysis. No malignancy is noted.<br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>C/W metastatic carcinoma</title>
    <created>20161220T085356Z</created>
    <updated>20230621T023502Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">metastatic carcinoma</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: normal;">Section shows liver tissue cores infiltrated by neoplastic cells featuring enlarged and pleomorphic nuclei with?out obvious glandular differentiation. </span></div></div><div style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: normal;">Immunohistochemically, these tumor cells _.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: normal;">The overall findings, taken together with clinical information, are compatible with metastatic __ adenocarcinoma. </span></div></div><div><br/><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Cavernous hemangioma.</title>
    <created>20190809T050939Z</created>
    <updated>20240320T081910Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Liver, segment ___, ____ --- Cavernous hemangioma.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a piece of hepatic tissue measuring __ cm and _____ gm. It had been sectioned partially when received. A tumor is seen measuring ____ cm. It is located ___ cm from surgical margin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follow:</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows hepatic tissue with a demarcated nodule composed of cystically dilated spaces lined by bland-looking</div><div>endothelial cells. Immunohistochemically, the endothelial cells are positive for CD31, confirming the diagnosis.</div><div>The non-tumor liver parenchyma shows chronic inflammatory cell infiltrate around portal area.</div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Sections of tumor show prominent hyalinization and sclerosis with some obliterated spaces lined by bland-looking endothelial cells as highlighted by ERG, with associated SMA-positive pericytes.</div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Cholesterosis</title>
    <created>20180820T083017Z</created>
    <updated>20230821T083122Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Cholesterosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows aggregate of foamy macrophages in lamina propria. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic cholecystitis with adenomyoma</title>
    <created>20170313T072047Z</created>
    <updated>20231108T073156Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic cholecystitis with adenomyoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The gallbladder shows intact, chronically inflamed mucosa accompanied by formation of Rokitansky sinuses within the underlying muscular coat. Adenomyoma is seen, which is composed of branching and cystically dilated glands glands invaginating into muscular wall, accompanied by hyperplasia of smooth muscle. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic cholecystitis with cholelithiasis (with adhered liver tissue)</title>
