<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Cholelithiasis with acute cholecystitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections reveal partial mucosal destruction and inflamed wall that is infiltrated by  numerous polymorphonuclear as well as mononuclear cells in its lamina propia as well as the underlying muscular coat. The wall shows edema, hyperemia and extravasation of RBCs. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Acute cholecystitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections reveal partial mucosal destruction and inflamed wall that is infiltrated by  numerous polymorphonuclear as well as mononuclear cells in its lamina propia as well as the underlying muscular coat. The wall shows edema, hyperemia and extravasation of RBCs. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
